# CI gate — run before finishing Python work

Mirror [`.github/workflows/ci.yml`](.github/workflows/ci.yml) and [`CI.md`](CI.md).
Do not report a task complete until this gate passes with zero errors.

## When to run

After any edit to `src/`, `tests/`, or `pyproject.toml` — including refactors,
new modules, and test-only changes.

## Canonical one-liner (repo root, venv active)

```bash
ruff check src tests && ruff format --check src tests && mypy src/warehouse && pytest
```

Explicit venv binaries:

```bash
.venv/bin/ruff check src tests && .venv/bin/ruff format --check src tests && .venv/bin/mypy src/warehouse && .venv/bin/pytest
```

## Fix loop (required on failure)

1. `ruff check src tests --fix`
2. `ruff format src tests`
3. Re-run the full one-liner above — all four steps, in order.

Do not skip `mypy` or `pytest` because lint is clean.

## What each step enforces

| Step | Tool | Catches |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Lint | `ruff check` | **E**, F, I, UP (line-length 79; see `pyproject.toml`) |
| Format | `ruff format --check` | Unformatted Python |
| Types | `mypy src/warehouse` | Strict typing (`strict = true`) |
| Tests | `pytest` | Regressions |

**E501:** allowed only in `dashboard/server.py`, `dashboard/render_*.py`,
`phases.py`, `status.py` — nowhere else. No `# noqa: E501` elsewhere.

## Agent obligations

- **Run** the gate yourself; do not tell the user to run it unless blocked
  (missing venv, sandbox).
- **Fix** failures in the same turn when possible.
- **Report** only after all four steps pass (e.g. "234 passed, mypy clean").
